org.net4care.observation

Class StandardTeleObservation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.net4care.observation.StandardTeleObservation

  • public final class StandardTeleObservation
extends Object
    Any observation of clinical physical quantities (typically measured by some device in the home) is embedded in an object of this type that expresses the measurement context of the actual values measured. This entail device characteristics, organizational context and stewardship, etc. DO NOT CHANGE NAMING OF FIELDS NOR METHOD AS THE SERVER SIDE DESERIALIZER ARE DEPENDENT UPON THESE NAMES.
    Author:
    Henrik Baerbak Christensen, Aarhus University

      • StandardTeleObservation

        public StandardTeleObservation()
        Default constructor to have bean properties. Do not use this in client code. Provided only for serialization and deserialization.

      • StandardTeleObservation

        public StandardTeleObservation(String patientCPR,
                       String organisationOID,
                       String treatmentID,
                       String codeSystem,
                       DeviceDescription deviceDescription,
                       ObservationSpecifics obsspec)
        Create an observation. Precondition: All parameters must NOT be null.
        Parameters:
        patientCPR - CPR identity of the patient this observation is made on
        organisationOID - the unique Net4Care issued identity of the organization that operates the device that has made this observation
        treatmentID - Unique ID of the treatment (behandling) that this observation is part of. Any device set up in a patients home must be set there for a reason, namely as part of a treatment. That is a central (net4care) organization has stewardship/is responsible for authorizing a treatment - this treatment must be associated with a unique ID and the teleobservation must tell it belongs to this by refering to it.
        codeSystem - the coding system using HL7 OID that is used in all ClinicalQuantities defined in the ObservationSpecific delegate. Coding systems are typically LOINC (internationally) or UIPAC (Denmark). Consult the 'Codes' class for constants defining LOINC and UIPAC.
        deviceDescription - the description of the device this observation stems from.
        obsspec - the object that contains the actual measurements.

      • StandardTeleObservation

        public StandardTeleObservation(String patientCPR,
                       String organisationOID,
                       String treatmentID,
                       String codeSystem,
                       DeviceDescription deviceDescription,
                       ObservationSpecifics obsspec,
                       String comment)
        Create an observation. Precondition: All parameters must NOT be null.
        Parameters:
        patientCPR - CPR identity of the patient this observation is made on
        organisationOID - the unique Net4Care issued identity of the organization that operates the device that has made this observation
        treatmentID - Unique ID of the treatment (behandling) that this observation is part of. Any device set up in a patients home must be set there for a reason, namely as part of a treatment. That is a central (net4care) organization has stewardship/is responsible for authorizing a treatment - this treatment must be associated with a unique ID and the teleobservation must tell it belongs to this by refering to it.
        codeSystem - the coding system using HL7 OID that is used in all ClinicalQuantities defined in the ObservationSpecific delegate. Coding systems are typically LOINC (internationally) or UIPAC (Denmark). Consult the 'Codes' class for constants defining LOINC and UIPAC.
        deviceDescription - the description of the device this observation stems from.
        obsspec - the object that contains the actual measurements.
        comment - a (non-empty) comment that provides patient's remarks on the measurement.
